      "page_number": 1,
      "raw_text": "Supervising Architect j. X. Taylor\nof the government at Washington has\ndecided upon rough plans for the Spo-\nkane postoffice, which will be in prac-\ntically the same style as all the post,\noffices erected in cities of this size\nsince the Taylor regime commenced\nstone walls, slate roof, steel pillars\nand stringers. The lower floor will\nbe given over to the postal Offices\nthe second to federal courts and offices\nthe third to land office. Much consid\nGrafton is given to features of light and\nventilation."
    }
